{"session_id":"svc-1778363660017402614","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-09T21:54:22.032257004Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-150758e7-20260509T215413-e21b349a","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-150758e7\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003etests: move internal/server/perf behind //go:build perf tag; add make test-perf target\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  The cli/internal/server/perf package contains performance benchmarks\u0026#xA;  that run for ~80 seconds during the default lefthook pre-push\u0026#xA;  full-tests step. These are perf tests by intent, not unit tests; they\u0026#xA;  should not block every push. Today they have no build tag or skip\u0026#xA;  gate, so they run on every full-test invocation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CURRENT STATE\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/server/perf/ contains benchmark tests (e.g.\u0026#xA;    TestGraphQLPerfMatrix_Baseline) that take ~80s when not skipped.\u0026#xA;  - The package has a testing.Short() skip in some tests but not all,\u0026#xA;    and pre-push runs without -short.\u0026#xA;  - Makefile has a bench-graphql target (lines ~121-127) that writes a\u0026#xA;    Markdown baseline report when DDX_BENCH_REPORT_DIR is set, but it is\u0026#xA;    not invoked from CI today.\u0026#xA;  - .github/workflows/ci.yml does not invoke `make bench-graphql` or\u0026#xA;    otherwise run the perf package as a dedicated step.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Add `//go:build perf` tag to every test file in\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/server/perf/. Files to edit (run `ls\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/server/perf/*_test.go` and tag each).\u0026#xA;  - Update Makefile:\u0026#xA;      a. Add a `test-perf` target that runs `go test -tags=perf\u0026#xA;         ./internal/server/perf/...` with an appropriate timeout (e.g.\u0026#xA;         5 minutes).\u0026#xA;      b. Document that `make test` excludes perf; `make test-perf` runs\u0026#xA;         them.\u0026#xA;  - Update .github/workflows/ci.yml:\u0026#xA;      a. Add a new step or job that runs `make test-perf` on a schedule\u0026#xA;         OR on pull requests touching cli/internal/server/perf/. Don\u0026#39;t\u0026#xA;         run on every PR by default; perf is non-gating.\u0026#xA;  - Update lefthook.yml ci block (or full-tests step) only if it\u0026#xA;    explicitly references perf (it doesn\u0026#39;t appear to).\u0026#xA;  - Verify default `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./...` no longer pulls perf tests\u0026#xA;    in (they should be excluded by the build tag).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Other test packages outside cli/internal/server/perf/ (covered by\u0026#xA;    sister beads).\u0026#xA;  - Designing a perf-regression dashboard (separate concern; this bead\u0026#xA;    just gates the slow tests behind a tag).\u0026#xA;  - Removing the perf tests; they remain valuable, just not on the\u0026#xA;    default path.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - Sister bead: \u0026#34;lefthook pre-push: add -short gate\u0026#34; (independent — the\u0026#xA;    -short flip and the perf-tag move both reduce pre-push time, by\u0026#xA;    different mechanisms; they compose).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Every *_test.go file in cli/internal/server/perf/ has a //go:build perf tag at the top.\u0026#xA;2. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./... (no -tags=perf) reports zero tests run from cli/internal/server/perf/...\u0026#xA;3. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test -tags=perf ./internal/server/perf/... runs the perf tests as before.\u0026#xA;4. Makefile contains a test-perf target invoking the tagged build.\u0026#xA;5. .github/workflows/ci.yml contains a step or job that invokes make test-perf on an appropriate trigger (schedule, perf-touching PR, or manual workflow dispatch).\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./... green.\u0026#xA;7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:tests, area:server, kind:refactor, perf\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"bcc41f3a77c00618c1199941e858aff66cc6e7c5\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260509T215413-e21b349a","base_rev":"bcc41f3a77c00618c1199941e858aff66cc6e7c5","bead_id":"ddx-150758e7","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a","correlation_id":"ddx-150758e7:20260509T215413-e21b349a","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260509T215413-e21b349a/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"1c5b527f473ee67eed635104061afecdc884db54f16962ea5a8d9d9b9108c13a","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-24322774","worker_id":""}}}
